Coronavirus Diaries is a series of dispatches exploring how the coronavirus is affecting people’s lives.
I’m clapping for a different reason: I’m thanking them for helping me get through my miscarriage.
The ascenseur émotionnel—in French, moods ride elevators not rollercoasters—escalated along with the coronavirus.
When the coronavirus started surging in Italy, I canceled to safeguard our baby.
Then, Prime Minister Édouard Philippe shut down cafés, restaurants, and other businesses that weren’t “indispensable to daily life,” to slow the spread of the coronavirus.